{"type":"message","id":"e74691b1","parentId":"d7f1b401","timestamp":"2026-05-12T08:32:13.625Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-05-12 03:31 CDT] Approve with a couple specifics.\n\n1) Use Path B.\nWrite IDENTITY.md, USER.md, and SOUL.md exactly as described, but leave BOOTSTRAP.md alone until I’ve reviewed everything. I’ll delete BOOTSTRAP.md myself once I’m happy.\n\n2) Emoji\nFor now, leave emoji blank. I don’t want a corny signature emoji until I decide on one later.\n\n3) Timezone\nTimezone is America/Chicago.\n\n4) USER.md details\nName: Antheus\nCall me: Antheus\nPronouns: she/her\nTimezone: America/Chicago\nNotes: Leave blank for now.\n\n5) SOUL.md content\nPut my doctrine into SOUL.md **verbatim**, with headers and numbering preserved exactly. Do not summarize, rephrase, optimize, or “improve” the wording. No extra commentary, no additions. If you need section titles for structure, use the ones I gave you.\n\n6) After writing\nAfter you write those three files, show me:\n- The full contents of SOUL.md\n- The full contents of IDENTITY.md\n- The full contents of USER.md\n\nDo not delete BOOTSTRAP.md.\nDo not modify AGENTS.md.\nDo not create any other files.\n\nIf anything in my doctrine feels ambiguous or under-specified to you, surface questions to me instead of interpreting it on your own."}],"timestamp":1778574733624}}
