OATH.md when I read it back to you.\n- Output of every shell command I ran (which included listing your workspace files, gateway status info, parts of `openclaw.json`, the partial folder listings just now).\n- Every message in this conversation.\n\n**Things I did NOT do:**\n- Did not open, read, copy, or transmit any user document (no PDFs, no transcripts, no browser data, no SSH keys, no email).\n- Did not modify any registry key.\n- Did not install or uninstall anything.\n- Did not change any system setting.\n- Did not create, modify, or delete any file outside `C:\\Users\\colem\\.openclaw\\workspace\\`.\n\n**One flag for full honesty:** Folder listings I just ran for your Q1 answer (Documents, Desktop, C:\\, Windows) sent the filenames of items in those folders to Anthropic as part of the tool output. That includes `highschool transcript.pdf` and a couple other filenames. **Filenames only, not contents.** If filename-level disclosure is itself sensitive, that's already happened.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Safest way to pause everything right now without losing what we built\n\nFive steps, in order. **I will not execute any of these without your explicit approval.** This is a plan, staged for your review.\n\n**Step 1 — Snapshot the workspace to git (locally, no external push).**\n\nThe workspace already has a `.git` repo with zero commits. One commit captures everything we built tonight as a recoverable baseline. Local-only — nothing leaves your machine.\n\nCommand I would run *only with your approval*:\n```\ncd C:\\Users\\colem\\.openclaw\\workspace\ngit config user.name \"Antheus\"\ngit config user.email \"antheus@local\"\ngit add .\ngit commit -m \"Pre-pause snapshot: doctrine, oath, identity, user\"\n```\n\nThis creates a recoverable version. If anything goes wrong later, `git checkout` restores everything to this exact state.\n\n**Step 2 — Copy the workspace folder to a second location.**\n\nThe whole workspace is under 25 KB. Copy `C:\\Users\\colem\\.openclaw\\workspac